Here's how to handle draft persistence using MAUI's lifecycle events:

**1. Override lifecycle events in `App.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
    {
        var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);

        window.Deactivated += (s, e) =>
        {
            // Fires when app goes to background
            WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppLifecycleMessage("background"));
        };

        window.Activated += (s, e) =>
        {
            WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppLifecycleMessage("foreground"));
        };

        return window;
    }
}

// Simple message class (uses CommunityToolkit.Mvvm)
public class AppLifecycleMessage : ValueChangedMessage<string>
{
    public AppLifecycleMessage(string value) : base(value) { }
}
```

**2. In your notes page code-behind or ViewModel:**

```csharp
public partial class NotesPage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "notes_draft";
    private Editor _editor;

    public NotesPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        _editor = this.FindByName<Editor>("NoteEditor");

        // Restore draft on page load
        if (Preferences.ContainsKey(DraftKey))
            _editor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);

        // Listen for lifecycle messages
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Register<AppLifecycleMessage>(this, (r, m) =>
        {
            if (m.Value == "background")
                SaveDraft();
            else if (m.Value == "foreground")
                RestoreDraft();
        });
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, _editor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    private void RestoreDraft()
    {
        _editor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    // Clean up when draft is submitted
    public void ClearDraft() => Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);

    // Unregister to avoid leaks
    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Unregister<AppLifecycleMessage>(this);
        base.OnDisappearing();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`Preferences`** — built-in MAUI key-value store, ideal for small strings. For larger drafts, use `FileSystem.AppDataDirectory` with file I/O instead.
- **`WeakReferenceMessenger`** — from `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` NuGet package; decouples lifecycle detection from your page.
- **`Window.Deactivated`/`Activated`** — the cross-platform hooks for background/foreground transitions.
- Always **unregister** the messenger in `OnDisappearing` to prevent memory leaks.
